21/08/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Bono, lead singer of the Irish rock band U2, paid a surprise one-day visit to Sarajevo on Sunday (20 August), accompanied by his wife Ali. 
The couple attended the 12th edition of the Sarajevo Film Festival, which kicked off two days ago. 
The musician and humanitarian first came to Sarajevo in 1993 to support residents of the city under siege. 
He has visited repeatedly since then. 
Hollywood actor Nick Nolte also attended the festival on Sunday. 
(Nezavisne novine, Sarajevo Film Festival website - 21/08/06)
